title.narrative: INTEGRATED MGT. ACUTE MALNUT. SERVICES

description.narrative: Strengthened health system capacity to provide integrated management of severe acute malnutrition, which contributes to Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition, Early Detection And Treatment Of Malnutrition (Covid), Nutrition And Emergencies. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Increased coverage of equitable, quality and effective nutrition services among children under five years old.

title.narrative: Strengthened health system capacity to provide integrated management of severe acute malnutrition

description.narrative: 3,657;children with severe acute malnutrition;were;treated;in both mainland and Zanzibar, representing 46 percent of the annual target. The lives of;1,893;children who recovered from severe acute malnutrition were saved.;This was as a result of timely procurement of life-saving nutrition commodities, supply chain strengthening, and human resource capacity building on the treatment of SAM. All health facilities treating children for severe acute malnutrition achieved a recovery rate greater than 75 percent, a default rate less than 10 percent,;and a death rate less than 5 percent, in line with SPHERE Standards. | Status:Met | As-of Date:23/12/2021
